The IEBC has announced the date for the by-elections for Kiambaa Member of National Assembly and Muguga Ward MCA. In a Gazette notice on Monday, IEBC chairman Wafula Chebukati said both mini-polls will be held on July 15. Chebukati said each political party intending to participate in the by-election shall submit the names of the persons contesting in a party primary and the date of the party primary on or before May 3. Also, the political parties have until May 17 submit a list of persons nominated to contest in the two by-elections to the Commission. Parties have the same period to present candidates intending to vie through direct nominations. Candidates shall be allowed to hit the ground for campaigns on May 24 to July 12. The IEBC boss said all campaigns shall run from 7.00 a.m. to 6.00 p.m during the campaign period. The chairman added that the commission shall publish, in the Gazette, the names of the persons contesting within seven days of receipt of the names of the candidates. Muguga's by-election comes following the demise of Eliud Ngugi, who passed on in March at theÂ Kenyatta University Teaching, Referral and Research Hospital. Kiambaa Constituency lost its MP Paul Koinange to Covid-19 related complications on March 31.